The speaker of Niger State House of Assembly, Abdullahi Wuse has said that state governments are in bad shape financially and that Niger State needs to improve on its revenue base. Wuse said this yesterday while receiving the members of Nigerian Bar Association (NBA) Minna. He spoke on the backdrop of  the dispute between the labour union and the government over June salary. He noted that the current
financial situation has put all states in Nigeria in bad shape. He stated that the bad financial state was a product of the variables on national economy and noted that Niger State could do better with improved internally generated revenue which he said the House was poised to do through the Finance Committee of the House. “In this state we have a problem, our revenue base should be more than what we are collecting , we will look at the ways and manner revenues are collected. Is every person paying what is due to the government?” he asked. According to him, the House is unhappy about the poor revenue base of the state adding that if the issues of internally revenue are properly addressed, the state could come out of the poor financial state. On the dispute over June salary of civil servants, he said the Assembly was looking at ways to resolve the issues saying that by law salary is the right of the workers.